<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
#div1 {
  height: 100px;
  width: max(50%, 300px);
  border: 1px solid black;
  padding: 10px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>The max() Function</h2>

<p>Use max() to set the width of #div1 to whichever is largest: 50% or 300px.</p>

<p>Resize the browser window to see the effect!</p>

<div id="div1">Some text...</div>

</body>
</html>
